img_caption: This song relates to the type of person who does it all and keeps a smile on while doing it all. They put the pressure on themselves to never ask for help as their perfectionist nature doesn't allow them to. But all the while their lack of asking for assistance gets them into trouble as they now feel run down tired irritable and not being able to perform their best. The song takes a turn when it start to voice that “It’s ok to feel pain” and that “everybody needs help sometimes.” This song holds a special place in my heart because I am that person. Every time I sing this song it is a reminder that I need to let go of always striving to be “perfect” because “perfect” doesn’t exist. It is a reminder to accept and love myself imperfections and all.  What better way to challenge myself than to put out a live/ stripped down video. Voice cracks weird facial expressions and all. With that- I hope you all enjoy.  Special thanks to @markvogelmusic for accompanying me on this song and @kyledijamco for filming! :) <3  Link in bio
